ick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Originally a Spanish version of   Elizabeth  , which was coined by deletion of the first syllable and alteration of the final consonant sound to one that can normally end a word in Spanish. The name was imported into France in the early Middle Ages, and thence into England. It was a royal name, and its enduring popularity may have been enhanced by the fact that it was borne by a queen of England—  Isabella  (  1296–1358 ), daughter of  Philip IV  of France—even though she led a turbulent life and eventually had her husband,  Edward II , murdered."],"variants":[{"name":"Isabell","meanings":["Originally a Spanish version of   Elizabeth  , which was coined by deletion of the first syllable and alteration of the final consonant sound to one that can normally end a word in Spanish. The name was imported into France in the early Middle Ages, and thence into England. It was a royal name, and its enduring popularity may have been enhanced by the fact that it was borne by a queen of England—  Isabella  (  1296–1358 ), daughter of  Philip IV  of France—even though she led a turbulent life and eventually had her husband,  Edward II , murdered."]},{"name":"Isabelle","meanings":["form of   Isabel  , now in frequent use in the English-speaking world."]},{"name":"Isobella","meanings":["form of   Isabel  , which has been popular in England since the 18th century and has recently become the preferred form of the name."]},{"name":"Isobelle","meanings":["Originally a Spanish version of   Elizabeth  , which was coined by deletion of the first syllable and alteration of the final consonant sound to one that can normally end a word in Spanish. The name was imported into France in the early Middle Ages, and thence into England. It was a royal name, and its enduring popularity may have been enhanced by the fact that it was borne by a queen of England—  Isabella  (  1296–1358 ), daughter of  Philip IV  of France—even though she led a turbulent life and eventually had her husband,  Edward II , murdered."]},{"name":"Isobel","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Isabel ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Isabel was born about 1400, in Ragnall, Nottinghamshire, England, United Kingdom. She married John Croftes about 1425, in Ragnall, Nottinghamshire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter."},"et":{"Abt 1400–":"umbes 1400–Surnud","1396–Male":"1396–Surnud","1420–Female":"1420–Surnud","1400–Female":"1400–Surnud","1400":"1400","1420":"1420","Abt 1425":"umbes 1425","1396":"1396","Abt 1400":"umbes 1400","of Ragnall,, Nottinghamshire, England":"Ragnall, Nottinghamshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Ragnall, Nottingham, England, Great Britain":"Ragnall, Nottinghamshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Ragnall,Nottinghamshire,England":"Ragnall, Nottinghamshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"Abt 1400–":"noin 1400–Kuollut","1396–Male":"1396–Kuollut","1420–Female":"1420–Kuollut","1400–Female":"1400–Kuollut","1400":"1400","1420":"1420","Abt 1425":"noin 1425","1396":"1396","Abt 1400":"noin 1400","of Ragnall,, Nottinghamshire, England":"Ragnall, Nottinghamshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Ragnall, Nottingham, England, Great Britain":"Ragnall, Nottinghamshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Ragnall,Nottinghamshire,England":"Ragnall, Nottinghamshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"Abt 1400–":"environ 1400–Décédée","1396–Male":"1396–Décédé","1420–Female":"1420–Décédée","1400–Female":"1400–Décédée","1400":"1400","1420":"1420","Abt 1425":"environ 1425","1396":"1396","Abt 1400":"environ 1400","of Ragnall,, Nottinghamshire, England":"Ragnall, Nottinghamshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Ragnall, Nottingham, England, Great Britain":"Ragnall, Nottinghamshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Ragnall,Nottinghamshire,England":"Ragnall, Nottinghamshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Isabel est née environ 1400, à Ragnall, Nottinghamshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Elle a épousé J